description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Berkshire Surrey Pathology Services (BSPS) is a successful and progressive merged pathology network which is a contractual joint venture between Ashford &amp; St Peter’s, Frimley Health, Royal Berkshire and Royal Surrey County Hospitals NHS Foundation Trusts. It provides services to NHS Acute Trusts, CCGs, academic centres and the private healthcare sector undertaking approximately 20 million tests per year serving a population of 2 million. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic, forward thinking individual with excellent interpersonal skills to become part of our team; managing and developing the Support Service Department at BSPS. The role extends all the partner Trusts across the networks. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be expected to travel to all sites within BSPS as required.&lt;br /&gt;As a key member of the BSPS senior management team, you’ll have strong leadership skills with a proven ability to lead and sustain transformational change. You will be experienced in working effectively in an operational setting and leading teams in complex environments as well as demonstrating innovation with a clear focus on operational delivery. Strategic thinking and implementation, performance management, quality management skills, coaching skills and highly developed communications skills will be fundamental to your role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Patricia RUWONA, BSPS Chief Operating Officer, BSPS Chief Operating Officer, p.ruwona@nhs.net, 07585401116&lt;/p&gt;
